21/03/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Chairman of the Council of Ministers Adnan Terzic said Friday (19 March) that BiH should play an active role in easing tensions in the region. Terzic was speaking at an extraordinary session of the presidency that focused on the violence in Kosovo. That same day, Republika Srpska Parliament Speaker Dragan Kalinic warned about the possibility of violence in Kosovo spreading to BiH. He said the situation could set the peace and security process back significantly. (SRNA, Federation News Agency - 19/03/04)
